column5: Hey Folks, How you all doing, been trying to get on the new site here for a couple of weeks and have finally got the bugs worked out. Been awhile since I posted on the old board as well so I just wanted to say "Howdy". Chuck (BIGCHEV4x4) I tried to no avail to get on the board to get you out on the ice. Give me a shout, remember it is Trudeau in the book.  Take care guys, hope to see some familiar faces down at the spring fishing show. MR. MEGER give me a shout.  T.J and Rick, thanks for get me up and running, Ry
Great to have you back, Ry.  Things are a little different but mostly the same.
Now that that is taken care of .....
Welcome back, I was wondering where you got to...hope all is good with you and yours.  Maureen
Welcome back Ryan. Anything new in the west half of the city. If I remember right I think you moved to a new home at work.  Mike
Hey Ryan.  Welcome back.   I see skud has posted aswell. Must be cold outside,or maybe musky season is over.LOL

Good to see you folks still here as well.Mike, transferrred to station 131 at Yonge and Lawrence.  Brian, you going in the tourny this weekend??? Hope you are all having a great hardwater season so far, see you out there. Ry
Hey Ryan, if you're at Yonge and Lawrence maybe I'll pop in and say hey one day while I'm at work   Every now and then I drop of or pick up customers from the church right next door.  Maureen
I thought I saw your name on the list. Are you liking the change?
What tourney you talk,n about willis?
